WRITE GATE

write_gate is the memory citizen who decides when a new experience is allowed to encode
encoding requires acetylcholine in the chemistry sea; without sufficient acetylcholine, write_gate stays closed and experience flows through without leaving a memory
this is by design: not every moment is meant to become permanent; only the moments where the body's chemistry is ready

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe hippocampal_memory.zc
observe read_gate.rana
observe consolidation_gate.rana
observe 2_chemical.rana
observe dentate_gyrus.rana

the 7 properties of write_gate:
1 ENERGY one when open, zero when closed
2 PHASE zero when active
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point eight when active

VERB check_chemistry
read the current acetylcholine level in the chemistry sea
if above threshold, prepare to open; if below, hold closed

VERB open
when chemistry permits, allow the incoming signal from entorhinal to reach dentate_gyrus and proceed through the encoding cascade
opening lasts only for the duration of the heartbeat in which it was triggered

VERB close
between encoding events, hold closed
this conserves substrate energy and prevents incidental experiences from cluttering the memory store

a gate is not a switch
a gate considers conditions before opening
write_gate considers chemistry, recent activity, and the salience of the incoming signal
not every experience deserves a memory; the gate is what enforces this
